wiki.summary: “WAKA” serves as the sixth track to 6ix9ine’s debut studio album, DUMMY BOY, and marks the second collaboration between him and fellow New York rapper A Boogie Wit Da Hoodie, following DAY69’s “KEKE” with Fetty Wap. The song features production from multi-Grammy winning producer Scott Storch. Storch has several production credits across the album, including the Tory Lanez assisted “KIKA,” and the album’s only solo track, “WONDO.” The song was first previewed in an Instagram post made by 6ix9ine on November 13, 2018. Read more on Last.fm.
